==English==

===Etymology===
This salad was invented in 1924 by Caesar Cardini, an Italian-American restauranteur.

===Noun===
'''Caesar salad'''

# (gastronomy) '''Caesar salad''': salad generally made from romaine lettuce, croutons, parmesan cheese and coddled eggs.

